<paragraph id="8BEA36F1FFACFFE4FF0D7A8DF23EFA79" blockId="0.[136,1452,1156,1935]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">
A group of very similar taxa includes 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FDAD7A8DF7F2FB3D" authority="(Tulasne 1844: 141) Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" baseAuthorityName="Tulasne" baseAuthorityPageNumber="141" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[552,1279,1156,1179]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bracteosum">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FDAD7A8DF021FB3D" box="[552,812,1156,1179]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Cenostigma bracteosum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FCB97A8DF70AFB3D" author="Tulasne, L. R." box="[828,1031,1156,1179]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" pagination="65 - 195" refId="ref1232" refString="Tulasne, L. R. (1844) Legumineuses arborescentes de l'Amerique du Sud, decrites. Archives du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle 4: 65 - 195." type="journal article" year="1844">Tulasne 1844: 141</bibRefCitation>
) Gagnon &amp; G.P.Lewis
</taxonomicName>
in Gagon 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FAF17A8DF6A1FB3D" box="[1396,1452,1156,1179]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">et al.</emphasis>
(2016: 88), 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FE8C7AA1F1ADFB19" authority="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" box="[265,672,1192,1215]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nordestinum">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FE8C7AA1F2A2FB19" box="[265,431,1192,1215]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">C. nordestinum</emphasis>
Gagnon &amp; G.P.Lewis
</taxonomicName>
in Gagon 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FC937AA1F043FB19" box="[790,846,1192,1215]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">et al.</emphasis>
(2016: 90), 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FC527AA1F658FB19" box="[983,1365,1192,1215]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FC527AA1F7C6FB19" box="[983,1227,1192,1215]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="diversifolium" subSpecies="comb">
C. diversifolium 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2125798FFACFFE4FB0B7AA1F7C6FB19" box="[1166,1227,1192,1215]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">comb</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
. et stat. nov.
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FA167AA1F1D9FB45" authority="(Tulasne 1844: 139) Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" baseAuthorityName="Tulasne" baseAuthorityPageNumber="139" baseAuthorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyramidale">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FA167AA1F20CFB45" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">C. pyramidale</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FE947AC5F2D0FB45" author="Tulasne, L. R." box="[273,477,1228,1251]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" pagination="65 - 195" refId="ref1232" refString="Tulasne, L. R. (1844) Legumineuses arborescentes de l'Amerique du Sud, decrites. Archives du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle 4: 65 - 195." type="journal article" year="1844">Tulasne 1844: 139</bibRefCitation>
) Gagnon &amp; G.P.Lewis
</taxonomicName>
in Gagon 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FCCC7AC5F08CFB45" box="[841,897,1228,1251]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">et al.</emphasis>
(2016: 93), the two latter hitherto been considered varieties of the same species. These species are very similar in vegetative features and can be distinguished as pointed out in great detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FEF67B1DF2F3FA8D" author="Lewis, G. P." box="[371,510,1300,1323]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" refId="ref1021" refString="Lewis, G. P. (1994) Systematic Studies in Noetropical Caesalpinia L. (Leguminosae: Caesalpinioideae), including a revision of the Poincianella - Erythrostemon group. Ph. D. Thesis. University of St. Andrews, St. Andrews, 237 pp." type="book" year="1994">Lewis (1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FD8F7B1DF14CFA8D" author="Lewis, G. P." box="[522,577,1300,1323]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" refId="ref1072" refString="Lewis, G. P. (1998) Caesalpinia: a revision of the Poincianella-Erythrostemon group. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, London. 233 pp." type="book" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FDFA7B1DF024FA8D" author="Queiroz, L. P." box="[639,809,1300,1323]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" refId="ref1123" refString="Queiroz, L. P. (2009) Leguminosas da Caatinga. Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana, Feira de Santana. 913 pp." type="book" year="2009">Queiroz (2009)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FCB17B1DF76DFA8D" box="[820,1120,1300,1323]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FCB17B1DF738FA8D" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" baseAuthorityName="Tulasne" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[820,1077,1300,1323]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyramidale">Cenostigma pyramidale</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2125798FFACFFE4FBBB7B1DF76DFA8D" box="[1086,1120,1300,1323]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is promptly recognised by the articulated pedicels below the middle of their lengths (
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FD4F7B31F1EAFAE9" box="[714,743,1336,1359]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">vs.</emphasis>
articulated directly below the ovary region in the other three taxa). 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FF0D7B55F284FAD5" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" baseAuthorityName="Tulasne" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[136,393,1372,1395]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bracteosum">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FF0D7B55F284FAD5" box="[136,393,1372,1395]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Cenostigma bracteosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by its broadly ovate and showy bracts, and by larger lateral petals (
<quantity id="4CAD9B14FFACFFE4FB7F7B55F660FAD5" box="[1274,1389,1372,1395]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" unit="mm" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17 mm</quantity>
long) (
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FF147B89F3A3FA31" box="[145,174,1408,1431]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">vs.</emphasis>
not showy, ovate-lanceolate bracts and smaller lateral petals to 
<quantity id="4CAD9B14FFACFFE4FCCF7B89F09EFA31" box="[842,915,1408,1431]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
in the other three taxa). The two remaining species are distinguished from one another by the size of leaflets and bracts: those are greater in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FBC37BADF657FA1D" authorityName="Gaem" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Benth." baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1094,1370,1444,1467]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diversifolium">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FBC37BADF657FA1D" box="[1094,1370,1444,1467]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Cenostigma diversifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FF0D7BC1F226FA79" box="[136,299,1480,1503]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nordestinum">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FF0D7BC1F226FA79" box="[136,299,1480,1503]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">C. nordestinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F657AFFACFFE4FF387BE5F2EDF829" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEA36F1FFACFFE4FF387BE5F0A6F911" blockId="0.[136,1452,1156,1935]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FED37BE5F2ECF9A5" author="Lewis, G. P." box="[342,481,1516,1539]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" refId="ref1021" refString="Lewis, G. P. (1994) Systematic Studies in Noetropical Caesalpinia L. (Leguminosae: Caesalpinioideae), including a revision of the Poincianella - Erythrostemon group. Ph. D. Thesis. University of St. Andrews, St. Andrews, 237 pp." type="book" year="1994">Lewis (1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FE6A7BE5F125F9A5" author="Lewis, G. P." box="[495,552,1516,1539]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" refId="ref1072" refString="Lewis, G. P. (1998) Caesalpinia: a revision of the Poincianella-Erythrostemon group. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, London. 233 pp." type="book" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FDB87BE5F05EF9A5" authorityName="Gaem" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Benth." baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[573,851,1516,1539]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diversifolium">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FDB87BE5F05EF9A5" box="[573,851,1516,1539]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Cenostigma diversifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FC097BE5F75EF9A5" box="[908,1107,1516,1539]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FC097BE5F72AF9A5" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" baseAuthorityName="Tulasne" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[908,1063,1516,1539]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyramidale">C. pyramidale</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2125798FFACFFE4FBB47BE5F75EF9A5" box="[1073,1107,1516,1539]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(previously 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FB5A7BE5F218F981" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Benth." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pyramidale" variety="diversifolium">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FB5A7BE5F677F9A5" box="[1247,1402,1516,1539]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">C. pyramidale</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FF0D7819F218F981" box="[136,277,1552,1575]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">diversifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FECF7819F19FF981" authority="var. pyramidale" box="[330,658,1552,1575]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pyramidale" variety="pyramidale">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FECF7819F2EEF981" box="[330,483,1552,1575]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">C. pyramidale</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FD9C7819F19FF981" box="[537,658,1552,1575]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">pyramidale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively) are distinguished from one another by terminal leaflet size, inflorescence indumentum colour, bract size, region of pedicel articulation, and standard claw apex, which sufficiently qualifies these taxa as independent species in the context where they are inserted and considering the current knowledge about this group, in my opinion. The same author also cites a resemblance between 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FC467875F7C8F935" authorityName="Gagnon &amp; G. P. Lewis" baseAuthorityName="Tulasne" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[963,1221,1660,1683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bracteosum">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FC467875F7C8F935" box="[963,1221,1660,1683]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Cenostigma bracteosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FB7C7875F6A8F935" authorityName="Gaem" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Benth." baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1273,1445,1660,1683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diversifolium">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FB7C7875F6A8F935" box="[1273,1445,1660,1683]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">C. diversifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, species that may frequently be misidentified without reproductive material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36F1FFACFFE4FF3878CDF2EDF829" blockId="0.[136,1452,1156,1935]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">
In his book “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FEC278CDF2C5F97D" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[327,456,1732,1755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Caesalpinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FEC278CDF2C5F97D" box="[327,456,1732,1755]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Caesalpinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: a revision of the Poincianella-Erythrostemon group”, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FB9778CDF7ACF97D" author="Lewis, G. P." box="[1042,1185,1732,1755]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" refId="ref1072" refString="Lewis, G. P. (1998) Caesalpinia: a revision of the Poincianella-Erythrostemon group. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, London. 233 pp." type="book" year="1998">Lewis (1998)</bibRefCitation>
designated the gathering 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FF0D78E1F212F959" box="[136,287,1768,1791]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Gardner 6006</emphasis>
at K as first-step 
<typeStatus id="54EE8853FFACFFE4FE6578E1F14FF959" box="[480,578,1768,1791]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D72FFACFFE4FDE378E1F710F959" authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1870" box="[614,1053,1768,1791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Caesalpinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pyramidalis" variety="diversifolia">
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FDE378E1F060F959" box="[614,877,1768,1791]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">Caesalpinia pyramidalis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FC2178E1F710F959" box="[932,1053,1768,1791]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">diversifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. At that time there was no barcoding system for Neotropical specimens in the Royal Botanic Gardens herbarium (G.P. Lewis, pers. comm.), and the two sheets of that collection were further considered two different specimens, receiving two different barcodes. Hence, I herein propose a narrowing second-step lectotypification according to Art. 9.17 of the International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B00FFACFFE4FE867971F2D8F829" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Prince, M. J. &amp; Smith., G. F." box="[259,469,1912,1935]" pageId="0" pageNumber="150" pagination="159" refId="ref1261" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Prince, M. J. &amp; Smith., G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal article" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B921EAE3FFACFFE4FEDA7971F299F829" box="[351,404,1912,1935]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="150">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
